Ugali

Ingredients:

  • 4 cups water
  • 2 cups maize (corn) flour

Instructions:

  1. Bring the water to a boil in a large pot.
  2. Gradually add the maize flour to the boiling water, stirring continuously to avoid lumps.
  3. Reduce the heat to low and continue stirring until the mixture becomes thick and pulls away from the sides of the pot.
  4. Cover and cook for a few more minutes.
  5. Turn off the heat and let it stand for a few minutes before serving.

Nyama Choma

Ingredients:

  • 2 lbs beef or goat meat, cut into chunks
  • Salt to taste
  • Lemon or lime juice (optional)

Instructions:

  1. Preheat your grill to medium-high heat.
  2. Season the meat with salt and lemon or lime juice, if using.
  3. Place the meat on the grill and cook, turning occasionally, until it is well browned and cooked to your desired level of doneness.
  4. Serve hot with a side of Kachumbari or your favorite side dish.

Kachumbari

Ingredients:

  • 2 large tomatoes, chopped
  • 1 red onion, thinly sliced
  • 1 cucumber, chopped
  • 1-2 green chilies, finely chopped
  • 1 bunch of cilantro, chopped
  • Juice of 1 lemon
  • Salt to taste

Instructions:

  1. In a large bowl, combine the tomatoes, onion, cucumber, chilies, and cilantro.
  2. Add the lemon juice and salt, and toss to combine.
  3. Adjust seasoning to taste and serve immediately.
